I'm trying to make it so prettierd is only run when a prettier config file is present in the project root. 
You can modify the configuration to check for a Prettier config file before running prettierd. Here's how you can do it:

```lua
return {
  {
    'stevearc/conform.nvim',
    event = { 'BufWritePre' },
    cmd = { 'ConformInfo' },
    keys = {
      {
        '<leader>f',
        function()
          require('conform').format { async = true, lsp_format = 'fallback' }
        end,
        mode = '',
        desc = '[F]ormat buffer',
      },
    },
    opts = function()
      local prettier_config_files = {
        '.prettierrc',
        '.prettierrc.json',
        '.prettierrc.yml',
        '.prettierrc.yaml',
        '.prettierrc.json5',
        '.prettierrc.js',
        '.prettierrc.cjs',
        'prettier.config.js',
        'prettier.config.cjs',
        'package.json',
      }

      -- Function to check if any Prettier config exists
      local function has_prettier_config(bufnr)
        local filepath = vim.api.nvim_buf_get_name(bufnr)
        local root = vim.fn.fnamemodify(filepath, ':h')

        for _, config_file in ipairs(prettier_config_files) do
          if vim.fn.findfile(config_file, root .. ';') ~= '' then
            return true
          end
        end
        return false
      end

      return {
        notify_on_error = true,
        format_on_save = function(bufnr)
          local disable_filetypes = { c = true, cpp = true }
          local lsp_format_opt
          if disable_filetypes[vim.bo[bufnr].filetype] then
            lsp_format_opt = 'never'
          else
            lsp_format_opt = 'fallback'
          end
          return {
            timeout_ms = 500,
            lsp_format = lsp_format_opt,
          }
        end,
        formatters_by_ft = {
          lua = { 'stylua' },
          javascript = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
          typescript = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
          javascriptreact = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
          typescriptreact = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
          html = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
          css = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
          json = function(bufnr)
            return has_prettier_config(bufnr) and { 'prettierd' } or {}
          end,
        },
      }
    end,
  },
}
-- vim: ts=2 sts=2 sw=2 et
```

The key changes are:

1. Added a list of possible Prettier config files to check for
2. Created a `has_prettier_config` function that checks if any Prettier config file exists in the current directory or any parent directory
3. Changed the formatter definitions to use functions that return either `{ 'prettierd' }` or `{}` based on whether a Prettier config is found
4. Wrapped the `opts` in a function to allow for this dynamic behavior

Now prettierd will only run when one of the Prettier config files is found in the project directory or any of its parent directories. If no config file is found, no formatting will be applied.
